.TH "TEXTENCODER.ENCODE" "3JS" "June 28, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TextEncoder.encode \- TextEncoder: encode() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]TextEncoder.encode()\f[B]\f[R] method takes a string as
input, and returns a \f[CR]Uint8Array\f[R] containing the string encoded
using UTF\-8.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
encode(string)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]string\f[R]
A string containing the text to encode.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Uint8Array\f[R] object containing the UTF\-8 encoding of the
input string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]p\f[R] class=\(dqsource\(dq>Sample paragraph.</\f[B]p\f[R]>
<\f[B]p\f[R] class=\(dqresult\(dq>Encoded result:</\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] sourcePara = document.querySelector(\(dq.source\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] resultPara = document.querySelector(\(dq.result\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] string = sourcePara.textContent;

\f[B]const\f[R] textEncoder = \f[B]new\f[R] TextEncoder();

\f[B]const\f[R] encoded = textEncoder.encode(string);
resultPara.textContent = \(ga${resultPara.textContent} ${encoded}\(ga;
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
The \f[CR]TextEncoder\f[R] interface it belongs to.
